<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">MongoDB Installation</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">From the Packages Repo:<br /></font></span></div><div><font color="#929292"># Updates package repository catalogues:</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff2f92"> sudo</font> <b>pkg update -f</b></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Install fresh the MongoDB (ver. 2.6.12)</font></div><div>=&gt; sudo <b>pkg install<font color="#0096ff"> </font></b><font color="#0096ff">mongodb</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Edit the “/etc/rc.conf” and add the line</font></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">mongod_enable</span>=“<span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">YES</span>"</div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># To start the Server:</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff2f92"> sudo </font><b>service</b> <font color="#0096ff">mongod</font><font color="#008f00"> start</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># To verify if the Server is running:</font></div><div>=&gt;<b> netstat -an | grep</b> <font color="#0433ff">27017</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff2f92"> sudo</font><font color="#0096ff"> mongo</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># I was able to use the MongoDB from the iMAC OSX without any problems:</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#0096ff"> mongo</font> <b>192.168.100.250</b>:<font color="#0433ff">27017</font></div><div><hr /></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 18px;">From the Ports Source Tree</font></b></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#ff9300"># You must uninstall the MangoDB ( 2..6.x) and </font></div><div><font color="#ff9300"># remove the folder “/var/db/mongodb” folder first.</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Update the Ports Tree:</font></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#ff2f92">sudo</font><b> portsnap fetch</b><font color="#009193"> update</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Install the MongoDB ( ver. 3.6 )</font></div><div>=&gt; <b>cd</b><font color="#941100"> /usr/ports/databases/mongodb36</font></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#ff2f92">sudo</font><b> make</b></div><div><font color="#ff2f92"># This will require the "py27-setuptools” , but</font></div><div><font style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"># it will conflict with the "py36-setuptools” if it was installed!</font></div><div><font color="#ff2f92"># So, I had to remove the <span style="color: #ff2f92;"> "py36-setuptools” first.</span></font></div><div><font color="#929292"># The OPTIONS:</font></div><div><en-media hash="a2913d0daa7da0a8aaa5fb5563273174" type="image/png" /></div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff2f92"> sudo<b> </b></font><b>make install clean</b></div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> sudo </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">service</span> <span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);">mongod</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 143, 0);"> start</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> sudo</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"> mongo</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># It did NOT allow me to login to  the MongoDB from the iMAC OSX !</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"> mongo</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">192.168.100.250</span>:<span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">27017</span></div><div>( see the config file below to reolve this problem )</div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"><br /></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"><br /></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 24px;"><span style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold;">Configuring the MongoDB  Server</span></font></div><div># By default, the MongoDB Server runs on Port 27017</div><div># If you want to change the Port, edit the file</div><div># "/usr/local/etc/mongodb.conf”</div><div># Also, for the MongoDB version 3.x , only local IP 127.0.0.1</div><div># You need to tell the config file to allow the remote access.</div><div><span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">net:</span></div><div>        <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">port</span>: <font color="#009193">1968</font></div><div><font color="#ff40ff">        </font><font color="#929000"># Allow remote access:   </font><font color="#ff40ff">     </font></div><div>        <font color="#ff2f92">#bindIp: 127.0.0.1  </font><font color="#929292"># Listen to local interface only!</font></div><div>       <font color="#4f8f00"> bindIp: 127.0.0.1,192.168.100.250 </font><font color="#929292"> # Listen to local and remote IP's</font></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"><br /></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"><br /></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"><br /></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 64, 255);"><br /></span></div></en-note>